<HEAD>Iowa Puts Voter Registration Forms in Phone Books</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION> is distributing voter registration forms inside each copy of the new telephone book, and officials hope the process catches on in other states. `` In every election, fewer and fewer people vote in <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>,'' Secretary of State <PERSON> Elaine </PERSON> <PERSON> Baxter </PERSON> said Friday. `` We're making <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION> the leader in convenient voter registration procedures.'' Telephone books currently being distributed by <ORGANIZATION> US </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION>, the Denver-based regional phone company, include voter registration forms at the bottom of one of the instruction pages. The form can be clipped and mailed in an envelope to the county auditor. State income tax booklets that will be sent out at the end of the year also will include voter registration forms, under legislation enacted this year. <PERSON> Earl </PERSON> <PERSON> Mix </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> US </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> vice president, said <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION> is the first state in which the forms will be included in telephone books. He predicted other states would follow suit. `` I hope that this becomes a model for the voter registration process,'' he said. <LOCATION> US </LOCATION> <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> distributes nearly 2.2 million telephone books in <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION>, Mix said. There are more than 1.5 million registered voters in <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION>, and an estimated 500,000 eligible voters who are not registered, Ms. <PERSON> Baxter </PERSON> said.
