<HEAD>Deadly Virus Found in Three Monkeys</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FREDERICK, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Scientists who began examining the carcasses of 100 laboratory monkeys imported from the <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION> by a <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> firm say they have so far discovered three with the ebola virus, considered the deadliest virus to humans before AIDS was discovered. Health officials also say they are monitoring the 25 employees at the <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> research firm that had received the monkeys in October even though they believe the disease would have turned up in the employees by now if any had been infected. Officials said none of the employees have shown any symptoms. The monkeys had been shipped to <ORGANIZATION> Hazleton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Research </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Products </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Reston </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, a subsidiary of <ORGANIZATION> Corning </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Glass </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> that uses primates for cosmetics and drug testing. This is the first time the virus has been found in a non-human and the first time it had been found in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The discovery of the first infected monkey was announced earlier this week. `` We do n't know where they got the virus,'' <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Dasey </PERSON>, a spokesman at the <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Research </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Infectious </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Diseases </ORGANIZATION> at <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Detrick </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Frederick </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Md. </LOCATION>, said Friday. `` We're continuing to help <PERSON> Hazleton </PERSON> and public health officials determine how far it has spread through the monkey colony,'' he said. In mid-November, medical investigators helped <LOCATION