instead to donate to the AIDS Project <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. In <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Orleans </LOCATION>, the NO-AIDS task force displayed children's artistic conception of AIDS One simply had the word `` choose'' between the words `` AIDS'' and `` life,'' said <PERSON> Lisa </PERSON> <PERSON> Lee </PERSON>, a member of the task force. In <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, nearly 80 demonstrators were arrested Friday after they sat down on <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Avenue </LOCATION> in front of the White House to protest what they called the government's lack of leadership in the AIDS epidemic. Those taking part in the civil disobedience were among some 200 people who attended an earlier rally criticizing President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> for what they said was the government's inadequate support for AIDS research and services. At a conference at <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>, business leaders attended a variety of seminars on how to deal with acquired immune deficiency syndrome in the workplace. `` A lot more things like these need to be done,'' said <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Baumhaur </PERSON>, president of the Fuddruckers hamburger chain and keynote speaker at the conference. `` Every business will be impacted by AIDS. We ca n't ignore it.'' As of the end of October, the federal <ORGANIZATION> Centers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Disease </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Control </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> had recorded 112,241 cases of AIDS in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, with 66,493 deaths. AIDS is caused by a virus that damages the body's immune system, leaving victims susceptible to infections and cancer. It is spread most often through sexual contact, needles or syringes shared by drug abusers, infected blood or blood products, and from pregnant women to their offspring.
