<TEXT>
 Two small buses collided when their drivers tried to slap each other's hands in greeting, the <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nigeria </ORGANIZATION> reported Saturday. It said seven people died. The agency said the accident occurred in <LOCATION> Enugu-Ezike </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Anambra </LOCATION> state in the eastern part of the country. The two drivers were among the dead, the agency reported.
